abstract: Mitt Romney has so far raised more campaign donations from Wall Street than President Obama has, The New York Times reports.
snippet: Mitt Romney has so far raised more campaign donations from Wall Street than President Obama has, The New York Times reports.
lead_paragraph: Mitt Romney has so far raised more campaign donations from Wall Street than has President Obama, The New York Times reports. Goldman Sachs employees, for example, have given $350,000 to Mr. Romney and $45,000 to Mr. Obama. They donated more than $1 million to Mr. Obama in 2008. Read more »

headline.main: Romney Ahead in Race for Wall Street Cash
